🧪 Admin Tool – Test Scenarios (Production-Ready, SDET Version)
1. Authentication & Access Control
Verify user with valid role can successfully authenticate and access Admin Home
Verify user without required role is denied access to Admin Tool
Verify expired session forces re-authentication
Verify role-based access restricts modules (Questions, Checklists, Templates, Vendors, Publishing, Audit)
2. Admin Journey (Core Workflow Guardrails)
Verify user can complete end-to-end flow: authenticate → author → preview → publish
Verify system blocks publish when required schema, logic, or dependencies are incomplete
Verify preview detects breaking changes to active installs before publish
Verify system enforces lifecycle transitions (Draft → Review → Approve → Publish)
Verify version is incremented on each publish
Verify rollback restores previous stable configuration
3. Artifact Management
Verify user can create new artifact (Question, Checklist, Template, Vendor)
Verify user can edit draft artifact
Verify user cannot edit published artifact without versioning
Verify system prevents concurrent overwrite (last-write conflict or locking)
Verify pending changes are tracked and retrievable
4. Schema Configuration (Critical Layer)
Verify system persists field schema with correct metadata (type, label, storage)
Verify schema changes are version-controlled
Verify schema updates do not corrupt existing data
Verify schema changes trigger impact analysis
5. Field Data Types & Storage
Verify system supports:
text, number, boolean, date/time
relational references (IDs, foreign keys)
audit fields (created_at, updated_at, created_by)
file-backed inputs
Verify system stores raw values separately from formatted values
Verify currency formatting does not affect stored raw numeric value
Verify invalid data types are rejected at API and UI level
6. Validation Rules Engine
Verify required field validation blocks submission
Verify format validation (regex, length, constraints) is enforced
Verify validation rules execute consistently across UI and API
Verify invalid validation rules (e.g., broken regex) are rejected at config time
7. Applicability & Conditional Logic Engine
Verify conditional logic evaluates correctly based on:
product
install type
dealer context
region
Verify nested conditions are evaluated correctly
Verify conflicting rules are detected and blocked
Verify missing upstream attributes do not cause system failure
Verify logic is configurable (not hardcoded in code)
8. Dealer Context & Upstream Integration
Verify system consumes upstream attributes (e.g., dealer location, region)
Verify logic adapts dynamically based on upstream data
Verify missing or delayed upstream data is handled gracefully
Verify integration with external context providers (e.g., CRM)
9. Checklist Authoring & Dependencies
Verify checklist steps can be created, grouped, and ordered
Verify dependencies between steps are enforced during execution
Verify circular dependencies are detected and blocked
Verify ownership assignment is required and validated
10. Automation Mapping & Execution
Verify questions are correctly mapped to checklist steps
Verify triggers initiate correct downstream steps
Verify execution order follows dependency graph
Verify failure in a step triggers fallback logic
Verify escalation path is executed when defined
Verify system prevents execution when dependencies are unmet
11. File Import & Mapping Engine
Verify system accepts file uploads (CSV/Excel)
Verify column-to-field mapping is configurable
Verify mapping definitions are reusable
Verify transformation rules (mapping actions) are applied correctly
Verify mismatched schemas are handled via mapping layer
Verify invalid mappings are rejected before execution
Verify partial failures are reported with clear error details
12. Orchestration Map & Impact Analysis
Verify orchestration map reflects actual dependency graph
Verify map is read-only and consistent with backend state
Verify impact analysis identifies all downstream dependencies
Verify system flags breaking changes before publish
Verify impact analysis includes active installs
13. Preview & Simulation Engine
Verify preview renders configuration as actual runtime behavior
Verify simulation executes full workflow without persistence side effects
Verify simulation includes:
conditional logic
dependency execution
notification routing
Verify simulation fails when configuration is incomplete
Verify preview detects incorrect routing before publish
14. Notification & Multi-User Workflow
Verify notification is triggered on assignment
Verify assigned user receives correct task
Verify user can complete assigned step
Verify completion updates system state (UI + DB)
Verify duplicate notifications are not sent
Verify notification failure triggers retry or logging
15. Publish Lifecycle
Verify system enforces approval before publish
Verify publish creates immutable version snapshot
Verify rollback restores previous working version
Verify restore does not corrupt dependencies
Verify publish updates downstream consumers
16. Governance, Audit & Observability
Verify all configuration changes are logged with:
user
timestamp
change details
Verify audit logs are immutable
Verify version history is accessible
Verify system tracks usage and adoption metrics
Verify missing logs are detected as system failure
17. Data & Integration (High Volume / Real Ops)
Verify system supports large data ingestion (migration scenarios)
Verify ingestion does not block system availability
Verify hybrid flows (automation + manual review) work correctly
Verify partial ingestion failures are recoverable
Verify system integrates with data platforms (e.g., warehouse systems)
18. Performance & Scalability
Verify system handles:
2,500+ questions
100+ artifacts
concurrent admin users
Verify publish operation completes within acceptable SLA
Verify import processing scales with large files
Verify orchestration execution latency is within limits
